gomodel:SYNGO_4126  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig3B-D: CatD co-labels with GABAergic synaptic markers, vesicular GABA transporter (VGAT) or glutamic acid decarboxylase (GAD65/67), but not the glutamatergic presynaptic marker vesicular glutamate transporter type 1 (VGLUT1).\n\nFig3H: Double-immunogold labelling of CatD (15-nm particles) with GAD65 (10-nm particles) and VGLUT1 shows CatD localization within the endosome-like large vesicle at GABAergic terminals (H1 and H2), but not in VGLUT1-labeled excitatory synaptic terminals (H3 and H4). White arrowheads pointed to typical SVs, and the black arrowhead points to large endosome-like structures.\n\nFig3J: Quantitative analysis of CatD-positive vesicle sizes show that CatD-labeled vesicles are not conventional medium-size SVs but large ELVs.\n\nFigS3A-B: CatD colocalises with presynaptic marker synaptophysin in rat and human hippocampal slices.\n\nFigS5A-E: Western blot and immunofluorescence analysis using samples from CatD-deficient mice fail to detect CatD-positive protein bands and puncta indicating the specificity of the CatD antibody used.. Experimental description: Sprague Dawley rats were used for the immunogold EM and immunocytochemistry experiments. Human and mice brain slices were used for the immunohistochemistry experiments." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4126" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

